    "analysis": "Executor returned node-5 KPI discovery and a top-20 anomaly summary. What has been done: metric-level anomaly detection for frontend-0/1/2 revealed many persistent HIGH anomalies during the entire incident window (2022-03-21 12:00:00 → 12:29:59 CST) for KPIs whose names include 'container.node-5.*'. A node-level problem on node-5 is strongly suspected because the same continuous 30-minute anomalous runs (start 2022-03-21 12:00:00 CST) appear across multiple container/node KPIs for all three frontend pods. The top KPIs include network-related metrics (container_network_receive_err*, container_network_transmit_*), CPU load (container_cpu_load_average_10s), filesystem/IO metrics (container_fs_* /dev/vda1), and memory_failures metrics. Network KPIs were among the highest-ranked (total_anomalies 1050) while many FS/CPU/memory KPIs also show full-window anomalies (total_anomalies 990). What can be derived so far: node-5 is the predominant faulty node and the anomalous activity begins at 2022-03-21 12:00:00 CST. What remains uncertain: which resource category on node-5 (network, CPU, disk/FS/IO, or memory) is the primary underlying reason. To decide the root cause reason we need aggregated counts and earliest timestamps grouped by resource type across all node-5 KPIs so we can pick the dominant resource anomaly.",
