    "analysis": "So far we preprocessed metrics, computed global thresholds, and ran anomaly detection for frontend-0/1/2. Results show persistent, full-window HIGH anomalies starting at 2022-03-21 12:00:00 CST across many KPIs named with 'container.node-5.*'. Aggregation by resource group indicates disk_fs_io has the largest aggregated anomaly volume, followed by memory, CPU, threads/limits, and network. Error logs are concentrated on frontend-0/1/2, but the previous attempt to scan error_logs for filesystem/IO keywords returned no result (Executor returned None). To confirm the underlying reason (disk/FS/IO vs network vs memory) we must scan error_logs.csv for filesystem/I/O related messages and also report counts and earliest timestamps for frontend error logs in the incident window. This will let us corroborate metric findings with log evidence and determine the precise root cause reason and occurrence time.",
