Based on the metric, trace, and log analysis: persistent, full-window HIGH anomalies starting at 2022-03-21 12:00:00 (Asia/Shanghai, UTC+8) were observed across many KPIs labeled with "container.node-5.*", disk/FS/IO KPIs had the largest aggregated anomaly volume, traces show widespread error_rate spikes from frontends at the same time, and frontend error logs show repeated "failed to retrieve" warnings beginning at 12:00:00. These findings point to a node-level storage I/O issue on node-5 that began at the start of the incident window.

